snippet.textDisplay: The iPhone 13 is going to CRUSH this S20 Ultra expensive phone and make the $1,400 price tag seem like a discount. Oh wait there is sales tax for most people so allow that to sink in. Plus if you buy this phone it doesn't matter if it comes in pink, 99% who have a brain will buy a nice $50 to $100 case to protect it so that their investment doesn't go down because they dropped their phone on the concrete sidewalk or the kitchen floor. I bought a Samsung TV QLED from Costco for $1,199.99 plus sale tax and I know this TV is well worth the price tag. Phones are extremely overpriced and yes television's are as well we all know that. It's just funny how my 65' Samsung cost less money than a smartphone. In fairness, I just bought another TV but with tax it was $4,024 but this is the best TV man has made year to date. The SONY XBR-A9G 65' OLED TV is 2die4!! Bottomline is that we all have budgets. Someone may say I'm crazy for spending 4K on a bad ass television but if you go look they have this really nice but much bigger sized TV for $69,999.99. Yes a TV that cost about as much as a nice Tesla and more than a brand new Tesla Model 3. It's all relative. I can't afford a TV set that has a sales tax of $6,125 bucks....Just imagine giving the stupid state/Government over $6,000 bucks just so you can buy a TV set. Sorry for the long reply but I hate sales tax and I love this new Samsung S20 Ultra but that price tag keeps creeping up and up and up every year. And finally, there will come a day when these phones will cost more tan $2,000 a pop. Whomever gets this phone, please enjoy the hell out of it!! You deserve it 😎
